Chicken Cross Road Game Development

Weekly Project Report

Week 1: Project Initialization & Input System

Objective

The objective of Week 1 was to set up the development environment, create the project structure, and implement the basic game window, game loop, and keyboard input system for the Chicken Cross Road game.

Activities Completed

1. Development Environment Setup

- Installed Java Development Kit (JDK).
- Installed Visual Studio Code (VS Code).
- Installed Java Extension Pack in VS Code.
- Created a new Java project.

2. Project Structure Creation

Created the initial project files:

- Main.java
- GamePanel.java
- KeyHandler.java

3. Game Window Development

- Created the main game window using Java Swing (JFrame).
- Configured the window size (800 × 600 pixels).
- Disabled window resizing.
- Set the game title to Chicken Cross Road.

4. Game Loop Implementation

- Created a game thread.
- Implemented the main game loop using the Runnable interface.
- Refreshed the screen approximately 60 times per second.

5. Keyboard Input System

- Implemented keyboard controls using KeyListener.
- Configured movement using:
  - W – Move Up
  - A – Move Left
  - S – Move Down
  - D – Move Right

6. Player Representation

- Displayed a white square as the temporary player.
- Verified that player movement worked correctly.

Deliverables

- Main.java
- GamePanel.java
- KeyHandler.java
- Working game window
- Functional keyboard movement

Outcome

At the end of Week 1, a functional Java game window was successfully created with a working game loop and keyboard-controlled player movement.
